</emphasis>
P. 90; No. 1309. ‘London, 1 specimen’.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAA91118E33FFD0FF8CFC0D7050FC39" blockId="15.[113,1090,886,1119]" pageId="15" pageNumber="672">
<emphasis id="B9614D038E33FFD0FF8CFC0D700DFC14" bold="true" box="[113,303,966,985]" pageId="15" pageNumber="672">Original description.</emphasis>
‘C. flavescens, thorace immaculato, elytris ante marginem punctisque nigris. Habitat in nova Hollandia. Mus. Dom. 
<collectingRegion id="49D15FF38E33FFD0FECBFC2A704CFC39" box="[310,366,993,1012]" country="Gambia" name="North Bank" pageId="15" pageNumber="672">Banks</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAA91118E33FFD0FF6DFC377382FB92" blockId="15.[113,1090,886,1119]" pageId="15" pageNumber="672">
Statura omnino praecedentis [
<taxonomicName id="4C15EA928E33FFD0FE76FC377322FBC2" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1775" box="[395,512,1020,1039]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Cassida" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="672" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marginella">
<emphasis id="B9614D038E33FFD0FE76FC377322FBC2" box="[395,512,1020,1039]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="672">C. marginella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
]. Antennae flavae, apice nigrae.Thoracis clypeus rotundatus, flavus, integer. Elytra flavescentia, linea lata atra in medio interrupta, quae ante marginem a basi ad angulum ani excurrit. Margo ipse late flavescens fasciis duabus atris, altera ad basin, altera versus apicem. In disco obscuriore puncta aliquot nigra sparsa. Corpus subtus flavescens.’ (
<bibRefCitation id="EF84ECE08E33FFD0FDEDFB8773B4FB92" author="FABRICIUS J. C." bookContentInfo="(14) + 832 pp." box="[528,662,1100,1119]" firstAuthor="FABRICIUS" journalOrPublisher="O? cina Libraria Kortii, Flensburgi et Lipsiae" pageId="15" pageNumber="672" refId="ref18820" refString="FABRICIUS J. C. 1775: Systema entomologiae, sistens insectorvm classes, ordines, genera, species, adiectis synonymis, locis, descriptionibvs, observationibvs. O? cina Libraria Kortii, Flensburgi et Lipsiae, (14) + 832 pp." title="Systema entomologiae, sistens insectorvm classes, ordines, genera, species, adiectis synonymis, locis, descriptionibvs, observationibvs" type="book" year="1775">FABRICIUS 1775</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAA91118E33FFD0FF8CFBBC7286FB43" blockId="15.[113,1089,1143,1294]" box="[113,932,1143,1166]" pageId="15" pageNumber="672">
<emphasis id="B9614D038E33FFD0FF8CFBBC703CFB43" bold="true" box="[113,286,1143,1166]" pageId="15" pageNumber="672">Current status.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C15EA928E33FFD0FED8FBBC7282FB43" authority="(Fabricius, 1775)" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1775" box="[293,928,1143,1166]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Aspidimorpha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="672" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="interrupta" subGenus="Aspidimorpha">
<emphasis id="B9614D038E33FFD0FED8FBBC709EFB43" box="[293,444,1143,1166]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="672">Aspidimorpha</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B9614D038E33FFD0FE31FBBC7341FB43" box="[460,611,1143,1166]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="672">Aspidimorpha</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="B9614D038E33FFD0FD8FFBBC73FCFB43" box="[626,734,1143,1166]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="672">interrupta</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF84ECE08E33FFD0FD11FBBC72B5FB43" author="FABRICIUS J. C." bookContentInfo="(14) + 832 pp." box="[748,919,1143,1166]" firstAuthor="Fabricius" journalOrPublisher="O? cina Libraria Kortii, Flensburgi et Lipsiae" pageId="15" pageNumber="672" refId="ref18820" refString="FABRICIUS J. C. 1775: Systema entomologiae, sistens insectorvm classes, ordines, genera, species, adiectis synonymis, locis, descriptionibvs, observationibvs. O? cina Libraria Kortii, Flensburgi et Lipsiae, (14) + 832 pp." title="Systema entomologiae, sistens insectorvm classes, ordines, genera, species, adiectis synonymis, locis, descriptionibvs, observationibvs" type="book" year="1775">Fabricius, 1775</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAA91118E33FFD0FF8CFB5C723AFAC3" blockId="15.[113,1089,1143,1294]" pageId="15" pageNumber="672">
<emphasis id="B9614D038E33FFD0FF8CFB5C71C2FB63" bold="true" box="[113,224,1175,1198]" pageId="15" pageNumber="672">Remarks.</emphasis>
This name has been correctly applied since its description and the present identi¿- cation is in accordance with the 
<typeStatus id="54AE2FB38E33FFD0FE39FB7C70D7FB03" box="[452,501,1207,1230]" pageId="15" pageNumber="672">type</typeStatus>
. A detailed redescription of 
<taxonomicName id="4C15EA928E33FFD0FCE6FB7C7286FB03" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1775" box="[795,932,1207,1230]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Aspidimorpha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="672" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="interrupta">
<emphasis id="B9614D038E33FFD0FCE6FB7C7286FB03" box="[795,932,1207,1230]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="672">A. interrupta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was published by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF84ECE08E33FFD0FF68FB1C7072FB23" author="BOROWIEC L." box="[149,336,1239,1262]" firstAuthor="BOROWIEC" journalOrPublisher="Genus" pageId="15" pageNumber="672" pagination="121 - 184" part="3" refId="ref18452" refString="BOROWIEC L. 1992: A review of the tribe Aspidomorphini of the Australian Region and Papuan Subregion (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae: Cassidinae). Genus 3: 121 - 184." title="A review of the tribe Aspidomorphini of the Australian Region and Papuan Subregion (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae: Cassidinae)" type="journal article" year="1992">BOROWIEC (1992)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="EF84ECE08E33FFD0FEA1FB1C70D5FB23" author="ZIMSEN E." bookContentInfo="656 pp." box="[348,503,1239,1262]" firstAuthor="ZIMSEN" journalOrPublisher="Munksgaard, Copenhagen" pageId="15" pageNumber="672" refId="ref19364" refString="ZIMSEN E. 1964: The type material of I. C. Fabricius. Munksgaard, Copenhagen, 656 pp." title="The type material of I. C. Fabricius" type="book" year="1964">ZIMSEN (1964)</bibRefCitation>
reported just a single specimen in the BMNH, which was quite likely the only one Fabricius used for the description.
</paragraph>
